Large cooling holes along the rail reduce weight and aid in rapid cooling. Take advantage of M-LOK positions along the 3, 6, and 9 o’clock of the rail for all your favorite gear. An uninterrupted M1913 Picatinny top rail offers space to mount optics, sights, and other accessories with ease.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Winchester 94 Eastern Long Forearm 1949 Carbine in 32 W.S. Nice Vintage Deer Rifle!
postcontent: This Winchester Model 94 Eastern Long Forearm carbine is in amazing shape considering it's a 1949. The light spot on the rear of the stock in the first pic is a reflection. I can send updated photos. Everything is correct including the metal buttplate, beautiful bore and rifling, slight thinning of the blue along the lower receiver from being handled. Do not confuse the 32 W.S. (Winchester Special) with the 32 W.C.F. (Winchester Center Fire). The 32 W.C.F. later became the 32-20 and was a black powder cartridge. The 32 W.S. comes in with a velocity of just over 2400 feet per second and it's energy at just over 2100 foot pounds of force. Ot has a bullet diameter of .321 on a 30-30 case. The 32 W.C.F. velocity is 900 feet per second and energy is 207 foot pounds of force it was primarily for target and small game. It has a bullet diameter of .312. The 32 W.S. works great on large game and the ammo is readily available through Remington, Hornady, Federal and Winchester.

title: For Sale:  Belgian ZULU 1840's 12 GA BREECH LOADING MUST SEE!
postcontent: Very interesting Antique shotgun. Converted in the 1870's by surplus gun dealers into single shot breech loading shotguns for their rising African trade businesses with the tribes of the african american continent, hence given the nickname ZULU guns. Featuring a swing out breech block of simple design, they worked well enough for hunting, but not worth much in war. Very popular anyways, thousands were manufactured. This example has survived very well compared to most for the age. If you’re a collector in the market for one of these, this is a fine example to own! Metal Condition: Finish has worn to a silvery patina throughout, looks nice and consistent. Stock/Grips Condition: One piece stock is very well intact with a lovely surface. Bore: Bore is pretty dark with visible wear. Not unexpected for its age.
